#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:6
msgid "Installing and Using plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section talks about installing and using third party plugins. For "
"writing your own plugins, please refer to :ref:`writing-plugins`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:11
msgid "Installing a third party plugin can be easily done with ``pip``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:13
msgid ""
"pip install pytest-NAME\n"
"pip uninstall pytest-NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:18
msgid ""
"If a plugin is installed, ``pytest`` automatically finds and integrates it, "
"there is no need to activate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:21
msgid "Here is a little annotated list for some popular plugins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:25
msgid ""
"`pytest-django <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-django/>`_: write tests for "
"`django`_ apps, using pytest integration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:28
msgid ""
"`pytest-twisted <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-twisted/>`_: write tests "
"for `twisted <http://twistedmatrix.com>`_ apps, starting a reactor and "
"processing deferreds from test functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:32
msgid ""
"`pytest-cov <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-cov/>`__: coverage reporting, "
"compatible with distributed testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:35
msgid ""
"`pytest-xdist <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-xdist/>`_: to distribute "
"tests to CPUs and remote hosts, to run in boxed mode which allows to survive "
"segmentation faults, to run in looponfailing mode, automatically re-running "
"failing tests on file changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:41
msgid ""
"`pytest-instafail <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-instafail/>`_: to report "
"failures while the test run is happening."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:44
msgid ""
"`pytest-bdd <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-bdd/>`_: to write tests using "
"behaviour-driven testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:47
msgid ""
"`pytest-timeout <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-timeout/>`_: to timeout "
"tests based on function marks or global definitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:50
msgid ""
"`pytest-pep8 <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-pep8/>`_: a ``--pep8`` option "
"to enable PEP8 compliance checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:53
msgid ""
"`pytest-flakes <https://pypi.org/project/pytest-flakes/>`_: check source "
"code with pyflakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:56
msgid ""
"`oejskit <https://pypi.org/project/oejskit/>`_: a plugin to run javascript "
"unittests in live browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:59
msgid ""
"To see a complete list of all plugins with their latest testing status "
"against different pytest and Python versions, please visit `plugincompat "
"<http://plugincompat.herokuapp.com/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:63
msgid ""
"You may also discover more plugins through a `pytest- pypi.org search`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:71
msgid "Requiring/Loading plugins in a test module or conftest file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:73
msgid ""
"You can require plugins in a test module or a conftest file using :globalvar:"
"`pytest_plugins`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:75
msgid "pytest_plugins = (\"myapp.testsupport.myplugin\",)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:79
msgid ""
"When the test module or conftest plugin is loaded the specified plugins will "
"be loaded as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:84
msgid ""
"Requiring plugins using a ``pytest_plugins`` variable in non-root ``conftest."
"py`` files is deprecated. See :ref:`full explanation <requiring plugins in "
"non-root conftests>` in the Writing plugins section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:90
msgid ""
"The name ``pytest_plugins`` is reserved and should not be used as a name for "
"a custom plugin module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:97
msgid "Finding out which plugins are active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:99
msgid ""
"If you want to find out which plugins are active in your environment you can "
"type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:102
msgid "pytest --trace-config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:106
msgid ""
"and will get an extended test header which shows activated plugins and their "
"names. It will also print local plugins aka :ref:`conftest.py <conftest.py "
"plugins>` files when they are loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:113
msgid "Deactivating / unregistering a plugin by name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:115
msgid "You can prevent plugins from loading or unregister them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:117
msgid "pytest -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:121
msgid ""
"This means that any subsequent try to activate/load the named plugin will "
"not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:124
msgid ""
"If you want to unconditionally disable a plugin for a project, you can add "
"this option to your ``pytest.ini`` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:127
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:132
msgid ""
"Alternatively to disable it only in certain environments (for example in a "
"CI server), you can set ``PYTEST_ADDOPTS`` environment variable to ``-p no:"
"name``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/plugins.rst:136
msgid "See :ref:`findpluginname` for how to obtain the name of a plugin."
msgstr ""
